Privacy Policy
GardenTags Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 25th May 2018
We hope you get as much enjoyment as possible out of the GardenTags services. To enable you to do this it is important that you know where you stand when it comes to the collection, use, sharing and protection of your personal data.
Before we get down into the detail here are a few fundamentals you should know about our privacy principles:
Information and content you post and upload to GardenTags may be seen by others on the app and on our website.
We give you a number of options to control the privacy of your personal information and content . These options can be found in the app under Settings > Edit Your Profile
We may aggregate and then anonymise information about our members to use for business purposes
You can control how you hear from us. Your email options can be found in the app under Settings > Email Subscriptions
If you wish to delete all of your personal information and content from GardenTags please email us at
support@gardentags.com
and we will action this on your behalf
Be mindful that what you share, even if deleted, may still remain viewable and if shared outside our Services it may still appear
We take the privacy of our users very seriously. We ask that you read this privacy policy (“Policy”) which also includes our cookie policy, carefully as it contains important information about how we will use your personal data. We’ve tried to avoid jargon wherever possible however, if there is anything in our policy you don’t understand or would like us to clarify please don’t hesitate to contact us at
hello@gardentags.com
and we’ll try our best to help out. Or, if you prefer you can write to us at the following address:
GardenTags
Beau Pignon
6 La Grange Martin
La Grande Route de St Martin
St Hellier
Jersey
JE3 6JB
So here's the detail…
1. Introduction
The app, website, and other services are brought to you by 4D Media Limited (“we” or “us”) a company incorporated and registered in Jersey in the Channel Islands with registration number 118316. For the purposes of the Data Protection (Jersey) Law 2005, we are the 'data controller' (i.e. the company who is responsible for, and controls the processing of, your personal data).
We receive your personal information through a variety of means including our mobile app and our website
www.gardentags.com
. Collectively we call these our "Services".
By using our Services, you understand and agree that we are providing a platform for you to post content including but not limited to photos, comments and plant information that we share publicly. As such you consent to the collection, storage, transmission, transfer, adaptation, publication of your information and other uses as described in this Policy.
The Privacy Policy may change from time to time and, if it does, the up-to-date version will always be available on our Service. Please note that by continuing to use the service you are agreeing to any updated versions. This policy was last updated on 25 May 2018.
2. Information we collect from you
When you register
When you register for our Services we collect the following information - username, password, email address, date of birth, name, profile picture, certain biographical details (“Bio”), gardening experience level, gardening styles and location data. If you sign in with Facebook you give us permission to access your information from this service e.g. email address, friends list, interests and so on. The information we have access to through Facebook depends on your settings and/or
Facebook’s privacy policy
.
This information we collect helps secure and provide access to the services. It also enables us to provide a relevant experience to you.
Some of the information you provide during registration will be publicly available to other users of our Services. This will include your username, name, profile picture, information you supplied in your Bio and the country you are located in. This information will also be publicly available on the GardenTags website to all users and non-users of our Services. You can change what information is publicly available at any time by going into the app Profile > Settings > Edit your profile.
When you use our Services
When you use our Services we collect more detailed information about you based on how you use our Services and interact with other members. There is information you provide directly to us and information we collect indirectly when you use our Services. For example:
The content and information you share on the Service - garden and plant photos, comments you make, your contributions to the plant database, people you are following, photos and comments you like, photos and comments you tag, people who are following you, people you follow
Information and content you provide to help manage your garden. For example, plant task information and the notes you add to your plants, plants you add to your wishlist and premium tasks subscriptions you may purchase
Updated profile information - you may update your profile information at any time after registration, including your Bio. This information allows you to be found by other users of our Services.
Your location - When you use our Services, we collect and process information about your specific location. For the app to know your location you will be asked to give your consent to this when joining and from time to time during your use of the Services. Knowing your location helps us improve the Services including offering location specific plant tasks, planting recommendations and plants for sale in our price comparison. We may also share an aggregated and anonymised approximation of your location with our partners.
Communications between you and us – you provide us with your email contact information so we can better respond to your support requests and comments. We will keep a record of the email exchanges between us so we can better respond to future communications
Find Friends - this feature allows you to find friends that are using our Services. We can locate your friends on the app through (i) your contacts list on your device - in this instance we will access your device to look for users. We will always ask your permission to do this before we access your contacts (ii) third party social media sites such as Facebook - in this instance we will request you link your account to the social media site in doing so you understand that that the information you provide via this method is governed by this policy (iii) through a simple name and username search on
www.gardentags.com
Invite Friends - this works in a similar way to Find Friends. In this instance it will send them a message either via email, SMS , Twitter or a Facebook request to join. For invite friends via Facebook we will request access to your friend list on Facebook. Please note that you are responsible for any charges that apply to these communications. By selecting ‘Invite’ a friend you also confirm that you have the consent of the person whose details you are supplying. Please also be aware that we will let your invited friends know on the invite that you supplied his or her contact details
We use Google Analytics, Google Analytics demographics and interest reporting, and integrated services that require Google Analytics to collect data via advertising cookies and identifiers. Google Analytics is a tool that helps website and app owners to understand how their visitors behave on their websites and apps. This helps us improve the user experience and identify opportunities to enhance our Services wherever possible. It uses a set of cookies to collect information and report website usage statistics without personally identifying individual visitors to Google. It also uses some cookies set by other websites to help us understand more about our sites' visitors
Logging of your activity - a log of information is automatically generated and reported to us every time you use our Services e.g. if you upload a new garden photo. Our servers collect this log file information. The types of information logged include your IP (Internet Protocol) address, browser type, device used, location, page requested, how you entered and exited the app or website and what pages and actions you carried out whilst using our Services. When we send you an email we may also log if you opened the email and what links you clicked on in the email. We will also log what information you contributed to our gardening database
Identifying your device - as our Services include a mobile application it's important we understand from which device you are accessing our Services. To enable us to do this we may access, collect, monitor and store device identifiers on your device. The device identifier may deliver information to us about how you use our Services. This information will allow us to improve our Services and better personalise your experience of them.
Meta data - this is information that is associated with content which can either be added by us and/or users e.g. a hash tag which is added to a photo or piece of content that you publish. In the instance of a hash tag it makes your content more searchable by other users. It is also possible for us to add geographically related meta data that enables other users to search for the location of the content. Please note that we never publish your exact location.
Please note that any content you voluntarily share using our Services is made available to the public and can be re-shared, searched for and posted on other platforms such as Facebook which are outside our control
We shall not be liable to you or to any third party for any loss or damage resulting from content posted using our Services and you are responsible for displaying the personal data of any other person
Content shared or collected by our Services will also appear on those parts of our website which are publicly accessible for example your profile picture, bio and any comments or photos you post
3. Information about our use of cookies – our cookie policy
We use cookies to store and collect information about your usage of our website Services. Cookies are small pieces of information stored by your browser on your device’s hard drive. They send information back to our servers when you access our Services. They enable us to track your IP address, the browser and any search engine you use to arrive at our Services. You can find out more about cookies at www.allaboutcookies.org. If you continue to use our website Services we will assume that you are happy to receive all cookies. However, if you would prefer to change your cookie settings, you can do so at any time in your browser.
We use a limited number of cookies. We set our own cookie which captures limited site usage information and a Google Analytics cookie. As stated above we make use of a tool from Google called Google Analytics which tells us about the way people are using our Services. It uses cookies to detect that someone has been to the Services before, so that we can see how often people return, how long they stay, and where on the Services they tend to go. We use this to try to work out what kind of experience they're having so we can make it better.
We also use cookies from the following services:
Google Double Click For Publishers – this cookie enables us to serve relevant adverts to you across our Services
Affiliate Window, Webgains, Trade Doubler and Skimlinks – these cookies enables us to track what retailers you visit through our plant price comparison engine we may also be able to track what you buy. This enable us to fine tune the comparison engine so it serves you relevant plants and products.
Bit.ly – we use a service called Bit.ly that enables us to provide shorter links i.e. that don’t use up too many characters. Cookies are used to track who is clicking on the links
Strikingly.com – this is a service that enables us to create landing pages for GardenTags content. This service may use cookies.
Mailchimp – this service enables us to send out emails to you. They use cookies to track how you interact with the emails including what links you click on. This enables us to make the emails more relevant to you.
